imdb.plot: Takatoshi Tsuda joins Ousai Academy, a co-ed high school that until recently had been an all-girl school, where he is asked to join the student council as vice-president and a male representative.

episodes.title: Sakura no ki no shita de/Maikai tsuzuku kono kanji?!/Toriaizu nuidemiyouka
episodes.plot: On his first day at a new school, Takatoshi is coerced into becoming student vice-President. Since the school is almost all girls, they often seem to forget he's a boy and talk about disconcerting girl problems when he's around.

episodes.title: Toki ni kimi wa S ka M ka/Naraba kimi no sono chikara o tamesasetemoraou/Kirakira to kagayaku koitsu wa onushi no nanda?
episodes.plot: A girl at school nervously approaches Takatoshi.

episodes.title: Warenagara migoto na tsutsumiguaida/Kaichou! Motto suso o hirogechatte kudasai!/Mou manpuku nanoka?!
episodes.plot: Some of the student council go on a field trip. While away, a strange connection occurs between one of the travelers and one who remained behind.

episodes.title: Dakara mie naito Korode Chaku Kuzushi Teiru/omedetaa/dakara watashi hakoko madedeii
episodes.plot: The student council is together again. Gifts and double entendres are exchanged.

episodes.title: Oshiri, Taihen desho?/Yokkyou Fuman na dake da!/Watashi mo Pan o Kuwaete Toukou Shinakya!
episodes.plot: Takatoshi hallucinates due to a fever. The hallucinations aren't much stranger than his everyday interactions at school.

episodes.title: Tsuda-kun wa Yomanai wa! Tsukau no yo!/Uke ga Aru nara Seme ga Aru darou!/Iya, Fuku wa Kite Koi
episodes.plot: The student council investigates the legend of the school's ghost. They think it's fiction - until they hear eerie cries coming from the English resource room.

episodes.title: Dandan Oukiku natteku wa/Tsuda-kun wa Boizu Rabu
episodes.plot: It's summer and the school council goes to the beach with a teacher as chaperone. Their stay is extended when the chaperone runs amuck.

episodes.title: A?! Omae wa Asa no Ichigo Pantsu!/Fudeoroshi ga Hayaru kamo Shiren/Minna no Bun made Watashi ga Tatakau!
episodes.plot: The school's first co-ed sports festival is being planned. The girls of the student council lose all inhibitions when suggesting what new events should be in it.

episodes.title: Ikura de Kaimasu?/Naruhodo! Kankei Nai na! Oretachi!/Benezuera
episodes.plot: The head of the Disciplinary Club isn't pleased when Takatoshi makes the girls cry.

episodes.title: Meido wa Mita! Ojou-sama no Midara na (Ryaku)/Ore ni Sonna Kyara Settei wa NaiWatashi de Yokereba Tsukiau ga
episodes.plot: The student council visits Aria's mansion and are lead around by her offbeat maid.

episodes.title: Konna Seiri Genshou Mita Koto ga Nai/Shitagi mo Tsuketa Hou ga Ii?/Santa-san no Seiheki
episodes.plot: Takatoshi helps his sister with her studies and learns more than he cares to.

episodes.title: Ippanteki na Hajirai desu/Seifuku wa Han Nugi ga Suoba da yo/Kimi nari no Roshutsu Purei ja Nakatta no ka?
episodes.plot: A new year and time for the student council members to articulate their bizarre New Year's prayers and resolutions.

episodes.title: Seitokai Yakuindomo! Otsu!
episodes.plot: The student council shares flashbacks of the year's events. Some of them are what actually happened.

episodes.title: Kaettekita Seitokai Yakuindomo
episodes.plot: Takatoshi's sister starts attending his high school. He attempts to shield her from the blatant anatomical chatter, but usually fails. She doesn't mind.

episodes.title: Hanpanai Aniki/Jidoukai Yakuindomo
episodes.plot: The rest of the student council join Takatoshi and his sister in a talk about their lives together. There are details - way too many details.
